FIVE suspects have been arrested for allegedly assaulting a senior ANC councillor. The incident in Amathole District Municipality, Eastern Cape, took place on Monday, 24 January and a video soon went viral on social media. The video shows MMC for Strategic Management and Development Nanziwe Rulashe being dragged out of her office, allegedly by security officials. The video shows officials led by a woman who identifies herself as municipal head of security Phelela Phiti. Two men can be seen dragging Rulashe across the floor after storming her office and ordering her to vacate it. They tell her they were sent by the municipal manager. ANC provincial spokesman Loyiso Magqashela said: “This behaviour is unacceptable.” The municipality distanced itself from the alleged assault. A statement read: “This matter will be fully investigated and as the executive mayor, I will act accordingly.” Provincial police spokesman Brigadier Thembinkosi Kinana said on Tuesday, 25 January cases of common assault, malicious damage to property and intimidation were opened at Cambridge Police Station following the incident in East London “Five suspects, aged between 23 and 43, were arrested and later released on R500 bail each.The circumstances surrounding the incident are not clear at this stage as the investigation continues.”